sec.p:
The results obtained from the estimation of (1) for the crime classifications are reported in Table 1 using the whole sample period. In addition to providing the estimated values of the coefficient of interest (


β

), one-sided p-values against the alternative of a negative true value are also reported to assess the significance of the test statistic. From inspection of the results in Table 1, it can be seen that, for all crime series, highly significant evidence of β-convergence is detected with negative coefficients and very low p-values reported. A large degree of variation in the size of the estimated coefficients is apparent, with the greatest degree of convergence witnessed for rape, larceny and property crime in general, while the lowest level of convergence is detected for murder.
